summary: I know everyone is happy that J.J. Abrams is back for Episode 9, and will hopefully fix all of Rian Johnson's fuck-ups from TLJ....
body: I know everyone is happy that J.J. Abrams is back for Episode 9, and will hopefully fix all of Rian Johnson’s fuck-ups from TLJ. But Chris Terrio is co-writing. He wrote BvS and Justice League; notable disasters. Yes, he also wrote Argo, but Argo isn’t a big budget blockbuster. Way different set of writing challenges there. So Episode 9 has just as big of a chance being a flaming garbage pile like TLJ was. Hopefully J.J. will reign in Terrio’s weaker writing points, and his sexist tendencies so Rey won’t get further ruined. Cause if J.J. just lets him go wild like he did with Rian Johnson, I fear for Episode 9 very very much.

body:
Rebel Scum Villanelle

“Rebel scum,” a praise, a toast

What on earth are we fighting for?

In what, my friend, will you boast?


As children we all yearned to join the misfit host

To stand with the Jedi way

“Rebel scum!” A praise! A toast!

And those in the profession of arms, who serve from coast to coast

Who man the walls from day to day

In what, my friend, will you boast?

We started with the best intentions, with good we were engrossed

But in every deed, could we say:

“Rebel scum!” A praise? A toast?

For somewhere along the road, as we stood our post

In our hearts, the Empire’s flag held sway

In what, my friend, will you boast?

It’s not too late to turn back—to heed Yoda’s ghost

Just remember; “Hate is not the Jedi way.”

“Rebel scum?” A praise. A toast.

In what, my friend, will you boast?
